for example. If its substrate molecule is present at a concentration of 0.5 mM, which
is only one substrate molecule for every 105 water molecules, the enzyme's active
site will randomly collide with about 500,000 molecules of substrate per second. And
a typical globular protein will be spinning to and fro, turning about various axes
at rates corresponding to a million rotations per second.},
